<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8345653>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Cyrtopodium izaguirreae. A. Habitat. General view of the Bosques Serranos in the northern region of Uruguay. B. Plant in situ at the start of vegetative and reproductive growth. C. Details of the pseudobulbs, new shoots and inflorescence at the beginning of budding. D. Plant in situ with fully developed flowers and leaves. All photos from Rivera, Uruguay, by A. González." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8345653/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8345656>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Cyrtopodium izaguirreae. A. Uprooted pseudobulbs and roots. B. Upper part of pseudobulbs and leaves. C. Habit at anthesis. D.Inflorescence.E. Flower, frontview.F. Flower, back view.G. Flower, lateral view.H. Flower, lateralview with the lip forced downwards. I. Dissected perianth. J. Pedicellate ovary, column and lip, lateral view. K. Lip dissected. L. Base of the lip, showing the indument on the adaxial side. M. Callus, frontal view. N. Column, ventral view and base of the unguicule.All images from the same population of the type material (A. Gonzalez et al. s.n., MHNH 23501), images by A. González." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8345656/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8345660>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Cyrtopodium brandonianum, C. izaguirreae, C. kleinii, C. lageanum, and C. pallidum based on the ecoregions of Olson et al. (2001), following the modified map by Turchetto-Zolet et al. (2013). Abbreviations for Brazilian states: BA, Bahia; DF, Distrito Federal; GO, Goiás; MG, Minas Gerais; MT, Mato Grosso; PR, Paraná; RS, Rio Grande do Sul; SC, Santa Catarina; SE, Sergipe; SP, S„o Paulo." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8345660/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8345662>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. A–D. Cyrtopodium brandonianum. E–H. Cyrtopodium lageanum. I–L. Cyrtopodium pallidum. M–P. Cyrtopodium kleinii. O. Cyrtopodium kleinii together with C. izaguirreae. A, E, I, M. Habit. B, C, F, G, J, K, N, O. Flowers, front view, showing variations. D, H, L, P. Perianths dissected. A–D. Brasília, Distrito Federal. A. (Batista et al. 2375, BHCB). B. (Oliveira 42, UB). C. (Batista 2353, BHCB). D. (Batista 145 & 350, CEN). E, F, H. Lages, Santa Catarina (Batista 1444, CEN). G. Diamantina, Minas Gerais (Batista & Martins 2221, BHCB). I, K. Serra da Moeda, Minas Gerais (Batista et al. 2326, BHCB). J. Lagoa Santa, Minas Gerais (Batista 2720, BHCB). L. Distrito Federal (Batista 19, 36 & 132, CEN). M, P. Lages, Santa Catarina (Batista 1443, CEN). N, O. Rivera, Uruguay (González & Antúnez s.n., MHNH 23503)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8345662/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

